    #usage.linkable-section
      %h2 Include an Accordion Component
      %ol
        %li Create an element or div. Include any desired attributes and content.
        %li
          Add the
          %pre accordion
          class to define the component.
        %li
          Accordion required accordion header and accordion body. Accordion header is used to collapse and exapand the
          accordion body.
      %h3 Configuration Options
      %p The table below lists the available classes and their effects.
      %table
        %thead
          %tr
            %th Class
            %th Effects
            %th Remarks
        %tbody
          %tr
            %td
              %span
                %pre accordion
            %td Defines an accordion component
            %td Required
          %tr
            %td
              %span
                %pre accordion-header
            %td Defines the accordion header.
            %td Required
          %tr
            %td
              %span
                %pre accordion-body
            %td Defines an accordion body
            %td Required
    %h2 Understanding Accordion Plugin
    #methods.linkable-section
      %h3 Methods
      %div
        %pre.h4.font-alt new PragmaAccordion(element)
        %p Activates your content as an Accordion element.
        %pre.h4.font-alt .toggleAccordion()
        %p
          Toggles the accordion visibility.
          %strong
            Returns to the caller before the collapsible element has actually been shown
            or hidden
          (i.e. before the
          %code shown.pragma.accordion
          or
          %code hidden.pragma.accordion
          event occurs).
    #events.linkable-section
      %h3 Events
      %p Accordion class exposes a few events for hooking into the functionality.
      %table
        %thead
          %tr
            %th Event Type
            %th Description
        %tbody
          %tr
            %td show.pragma.accordion
            %td
              This event fires immediately when the
              %pre show
              instance method is called.
          %tr
            %td shown.pragma.accordion
            %td This event is fired when an accordion element has been made visible to the user.
          %tr
            %td hide.pragma.accordion
            %td
              This event fires immediately when the
              %pre hide
              instance method is called.
          %tr
            %td hidden.pragma.accordion
            %td This event is fired when an accordion element has been hidden from the user.
